def vizualize(filename, pdb, cls):    
    with open(filename) as f:
        view = py3Dmol.view()
        view.addModel(f.read())
        view.setStyle({'hidden':0})
        view.setStyle({'cartoon':{'color':'grey', 'opacity':0.9}})
    MG = {'resn':'MG'}
    view.addSurface(2,{'opacity':1,'color':'teal'}, MG)
    MC = {'resn':'MC'}
    view.addSurface(2,{'opacity':1,'color':'red'}, MC)
#     view.setStyle({'resi':cls.resi.tolist()},{'stick':{'color':'red'}})
    view.addSurface(1,{'opacity':0.5,'color':'teal'}, {'index':cls.ids})
    view.addSurface(1,{'opacity':0.8,'color':'gold'}, {'resn':'AT'})
    view.addLabel(pdb)
    view.zoomTo()
    return display(view.show())
